description: DlComp: Downlink component measurements including minimum and maximum SINR values for specific cells in a given area and time.  dateTime: Timestamp of the measurement; Area_Name: Geographic area of the cell; CellId: Unique identifier of the cell; Id2: Redundant cell identifier; Id3: Ancillary identifier (likely unused); vsDataType: Data type identifier; vsDataFormatVersion: Version of data format; DlComp.dlCompMeasRprtMinSinr: Minimum reported SINR (Signal-to-Interference-plus-Noise Ratio); DlComp.dlCompId: Component ID; DlComp.dlCompMeasRprtMaxSinr: Maximum reported SINR.
